Northern Yemeni forces said Tuesday they had shot  down two helicopters from the rival south over a highway leading to Aden.
A military spokesman quoted by the North's official SABA news agency said  one of the helicopter pilots was captured. He said nothing about the other.
The spokesman also said northern forces fighting in Habilayn, 40  kilometers (25 miles) northeast of the southern stronghold of Aden had  inflicted heavy losses on southern forces and seized four tanks, two 130 mm  cannons and eight trucks.
